# Scripted active-card puzzle: Volcanic Hammer (burn, "any target").
#
# Volcanic Hammer is a 1R sorcery that deals 3 damage to any target. Here the
# script forces P0 to cast it at P1's Grizzly Bears (a 2/2). 3 damage to a
# 2-toughness creature is lethal (CR 120.6, 704.5g state-based action) so the
# Bears dies and goes to its owner's graveyard.
#
# Because Volcanic Hammer can target any of {P0, P1, the creature}, the engine
# DOES prompt for a target (it is not forced), so the inline `targeting` clause
# is what selects the Grizzly Bears.
#
# Aspects exercised (tracking issue: Card Compatibility: Volcanic Hammer):
#   - parses + castable as a 1R sorcery (spell cast)
#   - "any target" targeting resolves to a chosen creature
#   - 3 damage marked, lethal -> creature dies (creature died)
#   - dead creature lands in its owner's graveyard

[metadata]
Name:Action Script - Volcanic Hammer Kills a Creature
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 is driven by an action script that casts Volcanic Hammer (3 damage, any target) at P1's Grizzly Bears, killing it. Demonstrates scripted active burn against a creature target.

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Volcanic Hammer
p0battlefield=Mountain;Mountain
p0library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears
p1library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

[p0_script]
# Cast Volcanic Hammer at the Grizzly Bears. The inline `targeting` clause names
# the creature semantically (anti-overfitting: by card name, not a menu index).
cast Volcanic Hammer targeting Grizzly Bears

[assertions]
# The burn spell was actually cast by the script (active-card aspect).
spell cast Volcanic Hammer
# 3 damage killed the 2/2 (CR 704.5g lethal damage state-based action).
creature died Grizzly Bears
# The dead creature is now in its owner's (P1's) graveyard.
opponent graveyard contains Grizzly Bears
